    <h1>Buffalo Niagara International Airport Service</h1>
    <img src="/img/BNIA.jpg" width="240" height="182" alt="" />
         <p align="left"><strong>Metro is the best way to get to and from the airport</strong></p>
         
    
      <blockquote> 
        <p>Metro Bus service from the Buffalo Niagara International Airport is quick, inexpensive and easy to use. Routes actively serve downtown Buffalo and Niagara Falls, offering connections to points throughout the  region.</p>
        <p><strong>Airport-Downtown Express</strong> <br />
          This shuttle runs non-stop service between the airport and Buffalo's central business district, including the Metro Bus station downtown (Metropolitan Transportation Center.) One-way fare is $2.50 Service runs weekdays, approximately every 30 minutes, during peak drive time.
  Consult the schedule - <a href="/Routes/Route.aspx?rt=204">Route 204 </a></p>
        
        <p><strong>Metro Bus</strong><br />
          Regular Metro Bus service runs through the heart of the city. It is the most economical way to get to and from the airport. One-way fare is $2. Consult the schedules - <a href="/Routes/Route.aspx?rt=24">Route 24 Genesee,
  </a>, <a href="/Routes/Route.aspx?rt=27">Route 27 Erie County Home,
  </a>, <a href="/Routes/Route.aspx?rt=68">Route 68 George Urban</a> </p>
        <p><strong>Paratransit </strong><br />
          Metro Bus and Rail is fully accessible to passengers with special needs. Riders may also qualify for PAL service. <a href="/Paratransit/">Click here for more information about Metro's Paratransit Services </a></p>
      </blockquote>
